    <p><strong>Space-saving tip:</strong> For a 500 sq ft bakery, opt for under-counter refrigeration in the production area wherever possible. A 300-litre upright fridge takes about 0.6 sq m of floor space — the same as a valuable prep station. Under-counter units (60cm deep, 90cm wide) fit below your prep tables and free up wall space.</p>

    <h2>4. Proofing Cabinet</h2>
    <p>A proofing cabinet provides controlled heat and humidity for yeast-leavened doughs, giving consistent rise times and better volume. In India's variable climate — bakingly hot in summer, dry in winter — a proofer makes production more predictable year-round.</p>

    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Tray Capacity</th><th>Price Range (INR)</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Budget (Indian brand)</td><td>8–10 trays</td><td>₹22,000 – ₹40,000</td></tr>
